'''EGSY8p7'''（全稱'''EGSY-2008532660'''）是一個遙遠星系，[[光譜|光譜]][[紅移|紅移]]值''z'' = 8.68（{{link-en|測光紅移|photometric redshift}}的值為 8.57），相當於距離地球132億光年，代表它是138億年前[[大爆炸|大爆炸]]後5.7億年的星系。

==概要==
2015年7月，天文學家宣布EGSY8p7是發現時最古老，並且是經證實[[最遙遠的天體列表|距離地球最遙遠的天體]]，打破了2015年5月宣布的[[EGS-zs8-1|EGS-zs8-1]]紀錄。

EGSY8p7 的光在到達地球前看似受到[[重力透鏡|重力透鏡]]的影響，使該星系影像放大為原本的2倍。如果未經重力透鏡放大，天文學家就無法以現今技術觀測到。EGSY8p7與地球之間的距離是透過量測該星系的{{link-en|萊曼α線|Lyman-alpha line|萊曼α發射線}}紅移的值確認。因此EGSY8p7是已知觀測氫原子萊曼α發射線的天體中最遠的。

天文學家相當驚訝能在這樣的距離觀測到 EGSY8p7，因為根據[[ΛCDM模型|標準宇宙模型]]，早期宇宙充滿了中性氫原子雲，這些古老，甚至是距離地球較近的氫原子雲都可能吸收所有發射線。一個可能的解釋也許是早期宇宙[[再電離|再電離]] 時，中性氫原子雲是成團散布在宇宙中，而不是均勻分布，使EGSY8p7的氫原子萊曼α發射線得以在被中性氫原子雲吸收之前到達地球<ref name="Space.com-2015-08-05">{{cite news |url= http://www.space.com/30170-most-distant-galaxy-discovered.html |title= Ancient Galaxy Is Most Distant Ever Found |date= 5 August 2015 |first= Mike |last= Wall |publisher= [[Space.com|Space.com]] |accessdate= 2015-09-15 |archive-date= 2019-07-05 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190705020653/https://www.space.com/30170-most-distant-galaxy-discovered.html |dead-url= yes }}</ref><ref name="AstronomyNow-2015-08-06">{{cite press release |url= http://astronomynow.com/2015/08/06/a-new-record-keck-observatory-measures-most-distant-galaxy/ |title= A new record: Keck Observatory measures most distant galaxy |date= 6 August 2015 |publisher= [[凱克天文台|W. M. Keck Observatory]] |agency= [[Astronomy_Now|Astronomy Now]] |access-date= 2015-09-15 |archive-date= 2015-08-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150808201746/http://astronomynow.com/2015/08/06/a-new-record-keck-observatory-measures-most-distant-galaxy/ |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name="HuffPost-2015-07-15">{{cite news |url= http://www.huffingtonpost.com/mario-de-leo-winkler/the-farthest-object-in-th_b_7795982.html |title= The Farthest Object in the Universe |first= Mario De Leo |last= Winkler |date= 15 July 2015 |publisher= [[赫芬顿邮报|Huffington Post]] |accessdate= 2015-09-15 |archive-date= 2018-05-19 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180519024320/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/mario-de-leo-winkler/the-farthest-object-in-th_b_7795982.html |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name="DailyMail-2015-07-16">{{cite news |url= http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-3164703/A-galaxy-far-far-away-Astronomers-confirm-star-13-1-billion-light-years-away-distant-known-universe.html |title= A galaxy that rally IS far, far away: Astronomers confirm star system 13.1 billion light-years away 